{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772232690,"nonce":"BQzywRIRBlMyweeegmjLHVBENz8=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87um_z-","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/320","origin":"github"},"title":"gather-project-knowledge: fix data fidelity errors in profile generation","message":"## Summary\n\nThe `gather-project-knowledge` skill's first run ([unh_marine_autonomy#96](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/pull/96)) produced\nprofiles with factual errors in package listings and dependencies. A spot-check of 3 of 34\nprofiles found errors in all 3.\n\n## Errors Found\n\n| Repo | Profile claims | Actual (from `package.xml`) |\n|---|---|---|\n| `s57_tools` | 1 package: `s57_tools` | 4 packages: `marine_charts`, `s57_layer`, `s57_grids`, `s57_msgs` |\n| `vrx` | 3 packages: `vrx_gz`, `vrx_ros`, `vrx_urdf` | 5 packages: `vrx_gz`, `vrx_ros`, `vrx_gazebo`, `wamv_description`, `wamv_gazebo` |\n| `unh_marine_navigation` | 5 packages: `marine_nav`, `marine_nav_interfaces`, `marine_nav_tasks`, `marine_path_planner`, `marine_path_follower` | 7 packages: `marine_nav_behavior_tree`, `marine_nav_bt_task_navigator`, `marine_nav_utilities`, `marine_nav_crabbing_path_follower`, `marine_nav_interfaces`, `marine_nav_behaviors`, `marine_nav_tasks` |\n| `unh_marine_radar` | Key dep: `OpenCV` | OpenCV not in any `package.xml` |\n\nThe `workspace_overview.md` table has the same errors.\n\n## Root Causes\n\n1. **Multi-hop data loss**: Scan agents returned correct data → main agent synthesized\n   `workspace_overview.md` → profile-writing subagent used the overview (already wrong) as\n   source instead of raw scan data. Each handoff lost fidelity.\n\n2. **Directory names confused with package names**: `vrx_urdf` is a directory containing\n   3 packages, not a package itself. `s57_tools` is the repo name. The synthesis step used\n   directory names instead of `\u003cname\u003e` elements from `package.xml`.\n\n3. **Hallucination under context pressure**: With 5 large scan results in context, the\n   agent fabricated plausible package names (`marine_nav`, `marine_path_planner`) instead\n   of using the actual names from scan data.\n\n## Proposed Fixes to SKILL.md\n\n1. **Structured intermediate format**: Require scan results to produce a machine-readable\n   list (repo → packages from `\u003cname\u003e` in `package.xml`) that gets copied verbatim.\n\n2. **Validation step before commit**: Add a step: \"Before committing, verify each profile's\n   package list by globbing for `package.xml` files in the repo and comparing `\u003cname\u003e`\n   elements against what the profile claims.\"\n\n3. **Reduce handoff hops**: Either have scan agents write profiles directly, or have the\n   main agent write profiles one-at-a-time while reading raw scan data — don't delegate\n   profile writing to a subagent working from a natural language summary.\n\n## Context\n\n- First run: [unh_marine_autonomy#96](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/pull/96) (PR with the errors)\n- Issue that triggered the run: [unh_marine_autonomy#95](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/issues/95)\n- Skill definition: `.claude/skills/gather-project-knowledge/SKILL.md`\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}